On Wed, 29 Mar 2000, Chris Mason wrote:
>This won't solve the kernel.org problem, as it only promises that what is
>in the file has been written at least once, instead of making sure the
>entire file is there.
Of course. That solves only half of the problem: the security issue. OTOH
in a fileserver usually files gets not overwritten so reiserfs should take
care of the main concern.
For full data consistency I don't think it's possible without data
journaling.
